did.unittitle: Historic Ephemera Collection
did.abstract: This collection includes ephemeral materials, mainly printed items, on a wide variety of subjects, acquired from the mid-20th century onward from various sources.

scopecontent.p: Definition: Ephemera are "materials, usually printed documents, created for a specific, limited purpose, and generally designed to be discarded after use." (from A Glossary of Archival and Records Terminology by Richard Pearce-Moses). Pamphlets, admission tickets, performance programs, and trade cards are a few examples of ephemera.
This collection includes ephemeral materials, mainly printed items, on a wide variety of subjects, acquired from the mid-20th century onward from various sources.

arrangement.p: The collection is arranged alphabetically by subject. In some cases, unsorted or miscellaneous items are filed at the end of each subject grouping.

accessrestrict.p: This collection is open and available for research use.

prefercite.p: Manuscripts, Archives, and Special Collections, Washington State University Libraries, Pullman, WA.

acqinfo.p: The materials in this collection were received from many different sources, including old vertical files from the WSU Libraries and unaccessioned, unprocessed gifts. MASC staff gathered them into this collection, beginning in 2010.

accruals.p: This is an open-ended collection; additions are expected.

processinfo.p: MASC staff initially assembled this collection in 2010-2011. In 2016, approximately 130 additional items were interfiled.

relatedmaterial.p: This collection includes only a small fraction of the ephemeral materials available in MASC. Many more items are included in manuscript collections, special collections, university archives, and the WSU Publications collection. Some ephemeral items held in MASC are individually cataloged, and can be found by searching the WSU Libraries' online catalog.
One of the larger ephemera collections held by MASC is the Washington State University Ephemera and Realia Collection, 1905- (SC 010)

controlaccess.p: This collection is indexed under the following headings in the online catalog. Researchers desiring materials about related topics, persons, or places should search the catalog using these headings.
